tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All parameters are within normal limits except for a slightly low fasting glucose (68.9 mg/dL), which may indicate mild hypoglycemia. HbA1c is at the upper limit of normal, suggesting good long-term glycemic control but close monitoring is advised. Renal and electrolyte values are normal. No acute laboratory concerns.
